<h1>OPMS-DBA</h1>

<h3>
  Oracle Performance Monitoring System for Database Administrators and Developers
</h3>

<b>
  Main Features:
  <ul>
    <li>Real-time Oracle Database performance monitoring</li>
    <li>Session and SQL runtime analysis</li>
    <li>Wait Event and bottleneck detection</li>
    <li>AWR / ASH performance report analysis</li>
    <li>Tablespace and storage monitoring</li>
    <li>SQL Worksheet for query execution and tuning</li>
    <li>RAC and instance activity monitoring</li>
    <li>Oracle licensing and management pack configuration</li>
  </ul>
</b>

<br>

<h3>System Description</h3>

<p>
  OPMS-DBA is a web-based Oracle Database performance monitoring system
  developed to support Database Administrators (DBA) and software developers
  in monitoring, analyzing, and troubleshooting Oracle Database systems.
</p>

<p>
  The system provides real-time monitoring dashboards, session analysis,
  SQL performance diagnostics, wait-event tracking, and historical workload analysis
  using Oracle AWR and ASH data.
</p>

